post_cb({"43954808": {"CommentCount": "1", "ViewCount": "141", "CreationDate": "2017-05-13T15:25:56.143", "LastActivityDate": "2017-05-13T15:36:38.417", "Title": "Why is the move constructor defined and the assignment operator implicitly deleted?", "PostTypeId": "1", "Id": "43954808", "Score": "2", "Body": "<pre><code>struct Foo\n{\n    Foo() = default;\n    Foo(Foo&amp;&amp;) = default;\n};\n\nint main()\n{\n    Foo a, b;\n    a = b;\n   // ^ \n\n   return 0;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>error: use of deleted function 'Foo&amp; Foo::operator=(const Foo&amp;)'</p>\n<p>in g++4.6 -std=c++0x  it's ok.\nbut, in g++6.2 -std=c++11 it's error.\nwhy?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><c++11><gcc><g++>", "OwnerUserId": "5185790", "AnswerCount": "2"}, "43954921": {"ParentId": "43954808", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>Sam has explained why GCC 6.2's behaviour is correct.</p>\n<p>GCC 4.6's behaviour is simply due to incomplete C++11 support in that version (as evidenced by the \"experimental\" C++0x switch); C++11 was not fully supported until 4.8.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "560648", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "43954921", "Score": "3", "CreationDate": "2017-05-13T15:36:38.417", "LastActivityDate": "2017-05-13T15:36:38.417"}, "43954875": {"ParentId": "43954808", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>The answer is because the C++ standard says so:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_43954808_43954875_0\">[class.copy]</p>\n<p id=\"so_43954808_43954875_1\">If the class definition does not explicitly declare a copy\n  constructor, one is declared implicitly. If the class definition\n  declares a move constructor or move assignment operator, the\n  implicitly declared copy constructor is defined as deleted; otherwise,\n  it is defined as defaulted (8.4).</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>You can always declare a default copy constructor, in your case:</p>\n<pre><code> Foo(const Foo&amp;) = default;\n</code></pre>\n", "OwnerUserId": "3943312", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "43954875", "Score": "6", "CreationDate": "2017-05-13T15:32:14.603", "LastActivityDate": "2017-05-13T15:32:14.603"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_43954808_43954875_1": {"section_id": 456, "quality": 0.9629629629629629, "length": 26}}, "n3337": {"so_43954808_43954875_1": {"section_id": 447, "quality": 0.9629629629629629, "length": 26}}, "n4659": {"so_43954808_43954875_1": {"section_id": 479, "quality": 0.9629629629629629, "length": 26}}}});